title: Modern 2 Bedroom Flat in Lekki

title: 160 Austin St, Boston, MA 02136
description: Comfortable apartment with modern kitchen.

description: This beautifully updated garrison colonial sits on a level corner lot near George Wright Golf Course, offering classic charm, comfortable, stylish living with modern upgrades. description: Built in 2021 in the Walk Hill section of Roslindale/JP, this contemporary home offers modern living. The chef-inspired kitchen, with custom cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, stone countertops, and a spacious dining area, is the heart of the home.

title: Single Room in Fairmount Hill
description: Classic red brick colonial home situated on one of the best lots on Fairmount Hill. Borders the Brush Hill Historic District of Milton. Scenic views of the Blue Hills and gorgeous sunsets. Open, bright, and well-proportioned first floor. Chef's kitchen with Subzero and Thermador appliances, granite, and a large center island, abutting a spacious dining area. The front to back living room captures natural light throughout the day. It opens to a spacious porch overlooking Milton and the Blue Hills.

title: 4 Bedroom Duplex in Roxbury
description: This is an opportunity of a lifetime! The first floor has a large kitchen which flows through to a sizable dining room with a built-in hutch, leading into a charming living room with lots of natural light throughout. There is a first floor bedroom with a closet outside the bedroom (public records show this as a 3 bedroom home) which can be used also as an office. An additional plus is having a half bath and laundry area located on first floor.

title: Luxury 3 Bedroom Flat in Boston Landmark
description: At the turn of the century, this was one of Boston's largest homes. Recently, the magnificent estate was named Roslindale’s sole landmark by the Boston Landmark Commission. Entering through a gate in the hedgerow, a rustic drive passes through a small orchard of fruit trees ending atop a rise at the grand entrance. Inside, the beautiful hardwood is reminiscent of times gone by.
